\par \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 I started }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f2\fs22\kerning0\insrsid12675943 \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 with}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af2\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f2\fs22\kerning0\insrsid3167170 \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 
 the provided Project 2 skeleton and then rebuilt the scanner and parser to match the full grammar in the assignment requirements. The work was done incrementally so that each language feature could be added and verified before moving to the next one.

\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 
The lexical analyzer was expanded first. The scanner now recognizes the complete Project 2 token set, including integer, real, and character literals; alternate comment styles using // and --; the required keywords such as if, elsif, endif, fold, left, ri
\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 ght,\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2  real, and endfold; and all arithmetic, relational, and logical operators.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 
The parser was then rewritten to remove the EBNF notation from the assignment grammar and replace it with recursive Bison productions. This included optional parameter declarations, zero or more variable declarations, zero or more elsif clauses, and zero 
\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 or more switch cases. Operator precedence and associativity were encoded directly in the grammar instead of using Bison precedence directives, as required by the project. Separate p\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 
roductions were used for additive, multiplicative, exponentiation, unary negation, logical or, logical and, logical not, and relational expressions.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 
After the full grammar was in place, syntax recovery was added using semicolon-based synchronization and targeted error productions. Recovery points were added for function headers, variable declarations, statements, when clauses, and malformed case claus
\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 es. The listing module was also updated so the compiler reports line-oriented errors and prints separate le\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 xical, syntax, and semantic totals or Compiled Successfully when no errors are found.

\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 
The completed parser was built with win_bison, win_flex, g++, and mingw32-make in the local Windows environment. The provided positive and negative test cases were run to confirm that valid programs parse successfully and malformed programs continue parsi
\hich\af2\dbch\af31505\loch\f2 ng after the first error when recovery is expected.
\par 
